history.content: I'm taking Data 100 this semester and afaik the prereqs aren't enforced. I think the instructors are aware that some students haven't taken all the prereqs before taking Data 100 because this semester, Prof. Denero sent out an email containing links to videos which covered prerequisite content that would be required in the class. Specifically in your case, I think your lack of linear algebra isn't too big of a problem, depending on when the instructors plan to introduce the more mathematical aspects of the syllabus. Most of the math skills you'll need are things you can pick up as you go IMO. Since you're taking 54 concurrently, I don't think this should be a big problem.

I was wondering if Data 100 would be doable while taking 54 with it at the same time (I don't know any linear algebra at this point). Also, I was wondering if there is a "prerequisite form" that needs to be filled out in order to enroll in Data 100 if you haven't satisfied all of the prerequisites (I haven't taken Data 8). Do you need to email Josh Hug to ask if he will allow you enroll in Data 100 without Data 8, or have people had success in the past by just signing up for Data 100 and then getting it without satisfying all of the prerequisites and not filling out this form/emailing the professor? Any info would be great, thanks!
